#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:11
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading Online"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:18
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&suse; offers an intuitive graphical and a simple command line tool to "
"upgrade a running system to a new service pack. They provide support for "
"<quote>rollback</quote> of service packs and more. This chapter explains how "
"to do a service pack upgrade step by step with these tools."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid "Conceptual Overview"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:29
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&suse; releases new service packs for the &sle; family at regular intervals. "
"To make it easy for customers to migrate to a new service pack and minimize "
"downtime, &suse; supports migrating online while the system is running."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:35
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Starting with &slea;&nbsp;12, &yast; Wagon has been replaced by &yast; "
"migration (GUI) and Zypper migration (command line). The following features "
"are supported:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:43
#, no-c-format
msgid "System always in a defined state until the first RPM is updated"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:48
#, no-c-format
msgid "Canceling is possible until the first RPM is updated"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:53
#, no-c-format
msgid "Simple recovery, if there is an error"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "<quote>Rollback</quote> via system tools; no backup/restore needed"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:63
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use of all active repositories"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:68
#, no-c-format
msgid "The ability to skip a service pack"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "Online Migration Not Supported for Major Releases"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:75
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The online migration is <emphasis>only</emphasis> supported for migrating "
"between service packs. Online migration is <emphasis>not supported</"
"emphasis> for upgrading to new major releases. For details, see <xref "
"linkend=\"cha.upgrade-paths\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:81
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the offline migration to upgrade to a new major release. For details, "
"see <xref linkend=\"cha.upgrade-offline\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:88
#, no-c-format
msgid "Service Pack Migration Workflow"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:90
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A service pack migration can be executed by either &yast;, <command>zypper</"
"command> , or &ay;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:95
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before you can start a service pack migration, your system must be "
"registered at the &scc; or a local &rmt; server. &suse; Manager can also be "
"used."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:101
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Regardless of the method, a service pack migration consists of the following "
"steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:108
#, no-c-format
msgid "Find possible migration targets on your registered systems."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:113
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select one migration target."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:118
#, no-c-format
msgid "Request and enable new repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:123
#, no-c-format
msgid "Run the migration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:137
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The list of migration targets depends on the products you have installed and "
"registered. If you have an extension installed for which the new SP is not "
"yet available, it could be that no migration target is offered to you."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:143
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The list of migration targets available for your host will always be "
"retrieved from the &scc; and depend on products or extensions installed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:149
#, no-c-format
msgid "Canceling Service Pack Migration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:151
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A service pack migration can only be cancelled at specific stages during the "
"migration process:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:158
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Until the package upgrade starts, there are only minimal changes on the "
"system, like for services and repositories. Restore <filename>/etc/zypp/"
"repos.d/*</filename> to revert to the former state."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:165
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the package upgrade starts, you can revert to the former state by "
"using a Snapper snapshot (see <xref linkend=\"cha.snapper\"/> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:171
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the migration target was selected, &scc; changes the repository data. "
"To revert this state manually, use <command>SUSEConnect</command> <option>--"
"rollback</option> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:180
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading with the Online Migration Tool (&yast;)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:182
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To perform a service pack migration with &yast;, use the <guimenu>Online "
"Migration</guimenu> tool. By default, &yast; does not install any packages "
"from a third-party repository. If a package was installed from a third-party "
"repository, &yast; prevents packages from being replaced with the same "
"package coming from &suse;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This changes the behavior of all package operations, such as the "
"installation of patches or new packages."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:221
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Deactivate all unused extensions on your registration server to avoid future "
"dependency conflicts. In case you forget an extension, &yast; will later "
"detect unused extension repositories and deactivate them."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:243
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Run &yast; online update to get the latest package updates for your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:249
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Install the package <package>yast2-migration</package> and its dependencies "
"(in &yast; under <menuchoice> <guimenu>Software</guimenu> <guimenu>Software "
"Management</guimenu> </menuchoice> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:258
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Restart &yast;, otherwise the newly installed module will not be shown in "
"the control center."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:264
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &yast;, choose <guimenu>Online Migration</guimenu> (depending on the "
"version of &productname; that you are upgrading from, this module is "
"categorized under either <guimenu>System</guimenu> or <guimenu>Software</"
"guimenu> ). &yast; will show possible migration targets and a summary. If "
"more than one migration target is available for your system, select one from "
"the list."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select one migration target from the list and proceed with <guimenu>Next</"
"guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:280
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case the migration tool offers update repositories, it is recommended to "
"proceed with <guimenu>Yes</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:286
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<remark>toms 2015-09-09: FATE#319140</remark> If the Online Migration tool "
"finds obsolete repositories coming from DVD or a local server, it is highly "
"recommended to disable them. Obsolete repositories are from a previous SP. "
"Any old repositories from &scc; or &rmt; are removed automatically."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:295
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check the summary and proceed with the migration by clicking <guimenu>Next</"
"guimenu> . Confirm with <guimenu>Start Update</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:302
#, no-c-format
msgid "After the successful migration restart your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:309
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading with Zypper"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:311
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To perform a service pack migration with Zypper, use the command line tool "
"<command>zypper</command> <option>migration</option> from the package "
"<package>zypper-migration-plugin</package> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:318
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reduce Installation Size"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:319
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When performing the SP migration, &yast; will install all recommended "
"packages. Especially in the case of custom minimal installations, this may "
"increase the installation size of the system significantly."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:324
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To change this default behavior and allow only required packages, adjust the "
"<option>solver.onlyRequires</option> option in <filename>/etc/zypp/zypp."
"conf</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:329
#, no-c-format
msgid "solver.onlyRequires = true"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:330
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Also, edit the file <filename>/etc/zypp/zypper.conf</filename> and change "
"the <option>installRecommends</option> option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:334
#, no-c-format
msgid "installRecommends=false"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:337
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This changes the behavior of all package operations, such as the "
"installation of patches or new packages. To change the behavior of Zypper "
"for a single invocation, add the parameter <option>--no-recommends</option> "
"to your command line."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:344
#, no-c-format
msgid "To start the service pack migration, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:359
#, no-c-format
msgid "Register your &sle; machine if you have not done so:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:362
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;<command>SUSEConnect</command> --regcode "
"<replaceable>YOUR_REGISTRATION_CODE</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:365
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are an LTSS subscriber, make sure that the LTSS extension repository "
"is active."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:371
#, no-c-format
msgid "Run <command>zypper</command> <option>migration</option> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:374
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;<command>zypper</command> migration\n"
"Executing 'zypper  patch-check'\n"
"\n"
"Refreshing service 'SUSE_Linux_Enterprise_Server_12_x86_64'.\n"
"Loading repository data...\n"
"Reading installed packages...\n"
"0 patches needed (0 security patches)\n"
"\n"
"Available migrations:\n"
"\n"
"    1 | SUSE Linux Enterprise Server 12 SP1 x86_64\n"
"    2 | SUSE Linux Enterprise Server 12 SP2 x86_64"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:386
#, no-c-format
msgid "Some notes about the migration process:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:391
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If more than one migration target is available for your system, Zypper "
"allows you to select one SP from the list. This is the same as skipping one "
"or more SPs. Keep in mind, online migration for base products (&slsa;, "
"&sleda;) remains available only between the SPs of a major version."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:400
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, Zypper uses the option <option>--no-allow-vendor-change</option> "
"which is passed to <command>zypper</command> <option>dup</option> . If a "
"package was installed from a third-party repository, this option prevents "
"packages from being replaced with the same package coming from &suse;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:409
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<remark>toms 2015-09-09: FATE#319140</remark> If Zypper finds obsolete "
"repositories coming from DVD or a local server, it is highly recommended to "
"disable them. Old &scc; or &rmt; repositories are removed automatically."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:419
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Review all the changes, especially the packages that are going to be "
"removed. Proceed by typing <literal>y</literal> (the exact number of "
"packages to upgrade can vary on your system):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:424
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"266 packages to upgrade, 54 to downgrade, 17 new, 8 to reinstall, 5 to "
"remove, 1 to change arch.\n"
"Overall download size: 285.1 MiB. Already cached: 0 B  After the operation, "
"additional 139.8 MiB will be used.\n"
"Continue? [y/n/? shows all options] (y):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:427
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the <keycombo> <keycap function=\"shift\"/> <keycap function=\"pageup\"/"
"> </keycombo> or <keycombo> <keycap function=\"shift\"/> <keycap function="
"\"pagedown\"/> </keycombo> keys to scroll in your shell."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:434
#, no-c-format
msgid "After successful migration restart your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:441
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading with Plain Zypper"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:443
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you cannot use &yast; migration or the Zypper migration, you can still "
"migrate with plain Zypper and some manual interactions. To start a service "
"pack migration, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:451
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are logged in to a GNOME session running on the machine you are going "
"to update, switch to a text console. Running the update from within a GNOME "
"session is not recommended. Note that this does not apply when being logged "
"in from a remote machine (unless you are running a VNC session with GNOME)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:460
#, no-c-format
msgid "Update the package management tools with the old &sle; repositories:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:463
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;<command>zypper</command> patch --updatestack-only"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:466
#, no-c-format
msgid "If the system is registered, it needs to be deregistered:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:469
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;<command>SUSEConnect</command> --de-register"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:472
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Remove the old installation sources and repositories and adjust the third-"
"party repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:478
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Add the new installation sources, be it local or remote sources (for the "
"placeholder <replaceable>REPOSITORY</replaceable> , refer to <xref linkend="
"\"sec.upgrade-background.modules\"/> ):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:483
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"sudo <command>zypper</command> addrepo <replaceable>REPOSITORY</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:484
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also use &scc; or &rmtool;. The command for &sle; 12 SP1 on &x86-64; "
"is:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:488
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;<command>SUSEConnect</command> -p SLES/12.2/x86_64 "
"<replaceable>OPTIONS</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:489
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keep in mind, cross-architecture upgrades are not supported."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:492
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Zypper will display a conflict between the old and new kernel. Choose "
"Solution 1 to continue."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:496
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Problem: product:SLES-12.2-0.x86_64 conflicts with kernel &lt; 4.4 provided "
"by kernel-default-<replaceable>VERSION</replaceable>\n"
" Solution 1: Following actions will be done:\n"
"  replacement of kernel-default-<replaceable>VERSION</replaceable> with "
"kernel-default-<replaceable>VERSION</replaceable>\n"
"  deinstallation of kernel-default-<replaceable>VERSION</replaceable>\n"
" Solution 2: do not install product:SLES-12.2-0.x86_64\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:504
#, no-c-format
msgid "Finalize the migration:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:507
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;<command>zypper</command> ref -f -s\n"
"&prompt.sudo;<command>zypper</command> dup --no-allow-vendor-change --no-"
"recommends"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:509
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The first command will update all services and repositories. The second "
"command performs a distribution upgrade. Here, the last two options are "
"important: <option>-no-allow-vendor-change</option> ensures that third-party "
"RPMs will not overwrite RPMs from the base system. The option <option>--no-"
"recommends</option> ensures that packages deselected during initial "
"installation will not be added again."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:522
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rolling Back a Service Pack"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:524
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a service pack does not work for you, &sle; supports reverting the system "
"to the state before the service pack migration was started. Prerequisite is "
"a Btrfs root partition with snapshots enabled (this is the default when "
"installing &slsa; 12). See <xref linkend=\"cha.snapper\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:533
#, no-c-format
msgid "Get a list of all Snapper snapshots:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:536
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;snapper list"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:537
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Review the output to locate the snapshot that was created immediately before "
"the service pack migration was started. The column <guimenu>Description</"
"guimenu> contains a corresponding statement and the snapshot is marked as "
"<literal>important</literal> in the column <guimenu>Userdata</guimenu> . "
"Memorize the snapshot number from the column <guimenu>#</guimenu> and its "
"date from the column <guimenu>Date</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:548
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Reboot the system. From the boot menu, select <guimenu>Start boot loader "
"from a read-only snapshot</guimenu> and then choose the snapshot with the "
"date and number you memorized in the previous step. A second boot menu (the "
"one from the snapshot) is loaded. Select the entry starting with "
"<literal>SLES 12</literal> and boot it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:557
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The system boots into the previous state with the system partition mounted "
"read-only. Log in as &rootuser; and check whether you have chosen the "
"correct snapshot. Also make sure everything works as expected. Note that "
"since the root file system is mounted read-only, restrictions in "
"functionality may apply."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:564
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case of problems or if you have booted the wrong snapshot, reboot and "
"choose a different snapshot to boot from&mdash;up to this point no permanent "
"changes have been made. If the snapshot is correct and works as expected, "
"make the change permanent by running the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:570
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;snapper rollback"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:571
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Reboot afterward. On the boot screen, choose the default boot entry to "
"reboot into the reinstated system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:577
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check if the repository configuration has been properly reset. Furthermore, "
"check if all products are properly registered. If either one is not the "
"case, updating the system at a later point in time may no longer work, or "
"the system may be updated using the wrong package repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:584
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure the system can access the Internet before starting this procedure."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:590
#, no-c-format
msgid "Refresh services and repositories by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:593
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper ref -fs"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:596
#, no-c-format
msgid "Get a list of active repositories by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:599
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper lr"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:600
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Carefully check the output of this command. No services and repositories "
"that were added for the update should be listed. For example, if you are "
"rolling back from &slsa; 12 SP1 to &slsa; 12 SP2, the list must contain the "
"<literal>SP1</literal> repositories, and not the repositories "
"<literal>SLES12-SP2-Pool</literal> and <literal>SLES12-SP2-Updates</"
"literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:607
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If wrong repositories are listed, delete them and, if necessary, replace "
"them with the versions matching your product or service pack version. For a "
"list of repositories for the supported migration paths refer to <xref "
"linkend=\"sec.upgrade-background.modules\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:615
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Last, check the registration status for all products installed by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:619
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;SUSEConnect --status"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:620
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All products should be reported as being <literal>Registered</literal> . If "
"this is not the case, repair the registration by running"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:625
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;SUSEConnect --rollback"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:630
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you have successfully reverted the system to the state that was captured "
"immediately before the service pack migration was started."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:637
#, no-c-format
msgid "Upgrading with &susemgr;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:639
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&susemgr; is a server solution for providing updates, patches, and security "
"fixes for &sle; clients. It comes with a set of tools and a Web-based user "
"interface for management tasks. See <link xlink:href=\"https://www.suse.com/"
"products/suse-manager/\"/> for more information about &susemgr;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:647
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SP Migration allows migrating from one Service Pack (SP) to another within "
"one major version (for example, from &slsa; 12 SP1 to 12 SP2). For more "
"information, see the <citetitle>&susemgr; Best Practices</citetitle> , "
"chapter <quote>Client Migration</quote> , section <quote>Migrating SUSE "
"Linux Enterprise Server 12 or later to version 12 SP2</quote> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:655
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<link xlink:href=\"https://www.suse.com/documentation/suse-manager/\"/> , "
"version 3.1."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:663
#, no-c-format
msgid "Migrate from &opensuse; Leap to &productname;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:664
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can migrate an &opensuse; installation online to &productname;. The "
"procedure is analogous to <xref linkend=\"sec.upgrade-online.zypper\"/> , "
"but some additional steps are required. We recommend to run this procedure "
"on a test system that replicates your production setup before executing it "
"on the production system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:672
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To see for which &opensuse; Leap versions a migration is supported, read "
"<xref linkend=\"sec.upgrade-paths.supported\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sle_update_online.xml:677
#, no-c-format
msgid "Not All &opensuse; Packages Can Be Migrated"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:678
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &opensuse; repositories provide more packages than are available in the "
"&productname; repositories. If you have any of these packages installed, "
"they will no longer receive updates after the migration. These packages will "
"be removed when following the procedure below."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:685
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure that all packages you need for operating your system are available "
"in the &productname; repository. You can also check if the packages are "
"available in the &suse; Package Hub repository. For details, see <xref "
"linkend=\"sec.add-ons.package-hub\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:692
#, no-c-format
msgid "To migrate from &opensuse; Leap, execute the following procedure:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:697
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Switch to a TTY, for example by pressing <keycombo><keycap>Ctrl</keycap> "
"<keycap>Alt</keycap><keycap>F1</keycap></keycombo> . Then log in as "
"&rootuser;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:704
#, no-c-format
msgid "Install <package>SUSEConnect</package> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:705
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>zypper in SUSEConnect</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:708
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remove packages that produce file conflicts during the migration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:711
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>rpm -e --nodeps yast2-branding-openSUSE</command>\n"
"&prompt.root;<command>rpm -e --nodeps yast2-branding-openSUSE-Oxygen</"
"command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:715
#, no-c-format
msgid "Register at SCC to get the &productname; repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:716
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>SUSEConnect -r <replaceable>REGISTRATION_CODE</"
"replaceable> -p SLES/15.0/x86_64</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:719
#, no-c-format
msgid "List and disable all &opensuse; repositories on your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:722
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>zypper lr</command>\n"
"&prompt.root;<command>zypper mr -d <replaceable>REPO_IDS</replaceable></"
"command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:724
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Replace <replaceable>REPO_IDS</replaceable> with a space character separated "
"list of all enabled &opensuse; repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:730
#, no-c-format
msgid "Now add the modules you need for your installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:733
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>SUSEConnect --list-extensions</command>\n"
"[...]\n"
"&prompt.root;<command>SUSEConnect -p sle-module-basesystem/15.0/x86_64</"
"command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:736
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To have replacements for most Leap packages, we recommend to enable the "
"Basesystem, Desktop Applications, Server Applications and Legacy modules. "
"Additionally, we recommend to enable the &suse; Package Hub."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:744
#, no-c-format
msgid "Migrate installed packages to the &productname; repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:747
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;<command>zypper dup --force-resolution</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:750
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remove orphaned packages."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: sle_update_online.xml:751
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;<command>zypper rm $(zypper --no-refresh packages --orphaned | "
"gawk '{print $5}' | tail -n +5)</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sle_update_online.xml:754
#, no-c-format
msgid "Finally, reboot the system."
msgstr ""
